---
layout: layouts/base.njk
description: Knowledge Islands is a model for building, governing, and evolving knowledge across individuals, teams, and generations — treating knowledge not as a filing problem but as a civilisation question.
---

<!-- ═══ HERO ═══ -->
<section class="section-navy" style="padding: 6rem 0 5rem; position: relative; overflow: hidden;">
  <!-- Subtle cartographic grid overlay -->
  <div aria-hidden="true" style="position: absolute; inset: 0; background-image: radial-gradient(circle at 1px 1px, rgb(245 239 224 / 4%) 1px, transparent 0); background-size: 32px 32px; pointer-events: none;"></div>

  <div class="page-container" style="position: relative; text-align: center;">
    <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; color: var(--color-gold); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Knowledge Islands</p>

    <h1 style="font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem); font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-parchment); line-height: 1.1; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; max-width: 18ch; margin-inline: auto;">
      Knowledge is a civilisation&nbsp;question.
    </h1>

    <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 1.125rem; color: rgb(245 239 224 / 75%); max-width: 52ch; margin-inline: auto; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">
      Not a filing problem. Not a search problem. Not a productivity hack. Knowledge Islands is a model for building, governing, and evolving knowledge — across individuals, teams, and generations.
    </p>

    <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
      <a href="/philosophy/" class="btn-primary">Explore the Philosophy</a>
      <a href="/model/" class="btn-ghost-light">See the Model</a>
    </div>

