</section>

<!-- ═══ THE THREE LAYERS ═══ -->
<section class="section-parchment" style="padding: 5rem 0;">
  <div class="page-container">
    <div style="text-align: center; max-width: 52ch; margin-inline: auto; margin-bottom: 3.5rem;">
      <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; color: var(--color-teal); margin-bottom: 1rem;">The Foundation</p>
      <h2 style="font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3vw, 2.5rem); margin-bottom: 1rem;">Three layers. One journey.</h2>
      <p style="color: var(--color-ink-light); line-height: 1.7;">Knowledge Islands distinguishes carefully between information, knowledge, and wisdom — because the work of moving between them is precisely what islands are for.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem;">

      <!-- Information -->
      <div class="card-ki">
        <div class="symbol-circle">
          <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 22 22" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true">
            <rect x="3" y="3" width="7" height="7" rx="1" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
            <rect x="12" y="3" width="7" height="7" rx="1" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
            <rect x="3" y="12" width="7" height="7" rx="1" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
            <rect x="12" y="12" width="7" height="7" rx="1" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="divider-gold"></div>
        <h3 style="font-size: 1.375rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Information</h3>
        <p style="color: var(--color-ink-light); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Organised data. It exists independently of the reader — databases, documents, feeds, records. Structure without meaning.</p>
        <p style="font-style: italic; color: var(--color-sandstone); font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: 0.9375rem;">The terrain before it is charted.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Knowledge -->
      <div class="card-ki" style="border-color: var(--color-teal); box-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgb(61 138 138 / 12%);">
        <div class="symbol-circle symbol-circle-teal">
          <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 22 22" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true">
            <circle cx="7" cy="11" r="3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
            <circle cx="15" cy="11" r="3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
            <path d="M10 11 L12 11" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
            <path d="M4 7 Q11 3 18 7" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" fill="none"/>
            <path d="M4 15 Q11 19 18 15" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" fill="none"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="divider-gold"></div>
        <h3 style="font-size: 1.375rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Knowledge</h3>
        <p style="color: var(--color-ink-light); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Information interpreted and applied. It requires you — your context, your connections, your lived experience. It changes when you do.</p>
        <p style="font-style: italic; color: var(--color-sandstone); font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: 0.9375rem;">The island as it is inhabited.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Wisdom -->
      <div class="card-ki">
        <div class="symbol-circle symbol-circle-forest">
          <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 22 22" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true">
            <circle cx="11" cy="11" r="8" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
            <path d="M11 3 L11 6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <path d="M11 16 L11 19" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <path d="M3 11 L6 11" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <path d="M16 11 L19 11" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <circle cx="11" cy="11" r="2" fill="currentColor"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="divider-gold"></div>
        <h3 style="font-size: 1.375rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Wisdom</h3>
        <p style="color: var(--color-ink-light); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Knowledge used well. It is distinctly human, and it outlives you. It emerges through reflection over time — and across generations.</p>
        <p style="font-style: italic; color: var(--color-sandstone); font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: 0.9375rem;">The ancient forest at the island's heart.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ THE CYCLE ═══ -->
<section class="section-mist" style="padding: 5rem 0;">
  <div class="page-container">
    <div style="text-align: center; max-width: 52ch; margin-inline: auto; margin-bottom: 3.5rem;">
      <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; color: var(--color-teal); margin-bottom: 1rem;">The Cycle</p>
      <h2 style="font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3vw, 2.5rem); margin-bottom: 1rem;">Knowledge needs tending.</h2>
      <p style="color: var(--color-ink-light); line-height: 1.7;">Information doesn't become knowledge by itself. Islands stay alive through a continuous cycle — running at different cadences, in parallel.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 0; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); overflow: hidden;">

      <div style="padding: 2.5rem; background: white; border-right: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
          <span style="font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-border); line-height: 1;">01</span>
          <div>
            <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--color-teal);">The Harbour</p>
            <h3 style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin: 0;">Capture</h3>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--color-ink-light); line-height: 1.7;">Information arrives without immediate judgment. The harbour receives everything before the library decides what belongs. No filtering at the gate — only routing.</p>
      </div>

      <div style="padding: 2.5rem; background: white; border-right: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
          <span style="font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-border); line-height: 1;">02</span>
          <div>
            <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--color-teal);">The Routes</p>
            <h3 style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin: 0;">Connect</h3>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--color-ink-light); line-height: 1.7;">Material is contextualised and linked to existing knowledge. This is the transformation step — where received information becomes owned knowledge. Links form. Meaning emerges.</p>
      </div>

      <div style="padding: 2.5rem; background: white;">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
          <span style="font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-border); line-height: 1;">03</span>
          <div>
            <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--color-teal);">The Observatory</p>
            <h3 style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin: 0;">Reflect</h3>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--color-ink-light); line-height: 1.7;">Periodic review surfaces what's stale, updates what's changed, retires what's obsolete. Reflection is how the island stays honest — about what it knows and what it no longer does.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ THE GEOGRAPHY ═══ -->
<section class="section-parchment" style="padding: 5rem 0;">
  <div class="page-container">
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 5rem; align-items: start;">

      <div>
        <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; color: var(--color-teal); margin-bottom: 1rem;">The Home</p>
        <h2 style="font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3vw, 2.5rem); margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">An island has structure.</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--color-ink-light); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
          A Knowledge Island isn't a folder. It has a <strong>Capital</strong> — a civic centre with a Library at its heart and a Council Hall for governance. Knowledge enters through the <strong>Harbour</strong>, moves through <strong>Streams</strong> while it's in motion, and settles into the Library when it's canonical.
        </p>
        <div class="accent-gold" style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
          <p style="color: var(--color-ink); font-style: italic; font-family: var(--font-heading);">"The structure is not bureaucracy. It's cartography — a map that tells you where you are."</p>
        </div>
        <a href="/philosophy/" style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-forest); font-weight: 500; text-decoration: none; display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;">
          Read the full philosophy
          <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M3 8 L13 8 M9 4 L13 8 L9 12" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>

      <!-- Geography diagram -->
      <div>
        <div style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: 2rem; box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgb(26 32 48 / 6%);">

          <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; padding-bottom: 1rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);">
            <div style="width: 10px; height: 10px; background: var(--color-gold); border-radius: 50%;"></div>
            <span style="font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: 1rem; color: var(--color-ocean);">The Capital</span>
          </div>

          <!-- Library -->
          <div style="background: var(--color-mist); border-radius: 0.5rem; padding: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
            <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--color-ocean); margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Library</p>
            <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr; gap: 0.5rem;">
              <div style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light); border-radius: 0.375rem; padding: 0.5rem 0.625rem; text-align: center;">
                <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-teal); margin-bottom: 0.125rem;">📅</p>
                <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.6875rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-ink);">Calendar</p>
                <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.625rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">Time-bound</p>
              </div>
              <div style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light); border-radius: 0.375rem; padding: 0.5rem 0.625rem; text-align: center;">
                <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-ocean); margin-bottom: 0.125rem;">⛰</p>
                <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.6875rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-ink);">Pillars</p>
                <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.625rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">Owned knowledge</p>
              </div>
              <div style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light); border-radius: 0.375rem; padding: 0.5rem 0.625rem; text-align: center;">
                <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-forest); margin-bottom: 0.125rem;">🗺</p>
                <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.6875rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-ink);">Resources</p>
                <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.625rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">External reference</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Council Hall -->
          <div style="background: var(--color-mist); border-radius: 0.5rem; padding: 0.875rem 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem;">
            <span style="font-size: 0.875rem;">🏛</span>
            <div>
              <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-ink);">Council Hall</p>
              <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.6875rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">Governance space — decisions, not storage</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Divider -->
          <div style="border-top: 2px dashed var(--color-border); margin: 1.25rem 0;"></div>

          <!-- Streams + Harbour -->
          <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 0.75rem;">
            <div style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light); border-radius: 0.5rem; padding: 0.875rem; background: white;">
              <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">〜</p>
              <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-ink);">Streams</p>
              <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.6875rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">Knowledge in motion</p>
            </div>
            <div style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light); border-radius: 0.5rem; padding: 0.875rem; background: white;">
              <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">⚓</p>
              <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-ink);">Harbour</p>
              <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.6875rem; color: var(--color-ink-light);">Port of entry</p>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ TERRITORIES & AGENTS ═══ -->
<section class="section-ocean" style="padding: 5rem 0;">
  <div class="page-container">
    <div style="text-align: center; max-width: 52ch; margin-inline: auto; margin-bottom: 3.5rem;">
      <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; color: var(--color-gold); margin-bottom: 1rem;">The Wider Picture</p>
      <h2 class="heading-display-light" style="font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3vw, 2.5rem); margin-bottom: 1rem;">Islands don't stand alone.</h2>
      <p style="color: rgb(245 239 224 / 75%); line-height: 1.7;">Knowledge Islands form territories. Territories connect into archipelagos. And within each island, humans and artificial agents work together — through different interfaces, with different roles, but in the same cycle.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 3rem;">

      <div style="border: 1px solid rgb(245 239 224 / 15%); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: 2rem; background: rgb(245 239 224 / 4%);">
        <div style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">🏝</div>
        <h3 class="heading-display-light" style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 0.625rem;">Island</h3>
        <p style="color: rgb(245 239 224 / 65%); font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.6;">A discrete, self-contained body of knowledge with defined boundaries and internal geography. Operates its own cycle independently.</p>
      </div>

      <div style="border: 1px solid rgb(245 239 224 / 15%); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: 2rem; background: rgb(245 239 224 / 4%);">
        <div style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">🗺</div>
        <h3 class="heading-display-light" style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 0.625rem;">Territory</h3>
        <p style="color: rgb(245 239 224 / 65%); font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.6;">Islands organised and governed together. One island holds governance infrastructure for the whole — the Principal Island.</p>
      </div>

      <div style="border: 1px solid rgb(245 239 224 / 15%); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: 2rem; background: rgb(245 239 224 / 4%);">
        <div style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">🌐</div>
        <h3 class="heading-display-light" style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 0.625rem;">Archipelago</h3>
        <p style="color: rgb(245 239 224 / 65%); font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.6;">The larger structure when territories connect. A federated knowledge ecosystem with shared language but independent governance.</p>
      </div>

      <div style="border: 1px solid rgb(245 239 224 / 15%); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: 2rem; background: rgb(245 239 224 / 4%);">
        <div style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">🤝</div>
        <h3 class="heading-display-light" style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 0.625rem;">Agents</h3>
        <p style="color: rgb(245 239 224 / 65%); font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.6;">Human agents originate meaning and hold ratification authority. AI agents extend scale and recall. Both work in the same cycle — through different interfaces.</p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div style="text-align: center;">
      <a href="/model/" class="btn-ghost-light">Explore the Model</a>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ ARCADIA CTA ═══ -->
<section class="section-parchment" style="padding: 5rem 0;">
  <div class="page-container" style="text-align: center; max-width: 52ch; margin-inline: auto;">
    <div style="display: inline-block; background: var(--color-mist); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 50%; width: 4rem; height: 4rem; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; margin-inline: auto; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 28 28" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true">
        <path d="M14 3 L14 7" stroke="var(--color-ocean)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
        <circle cx="14" cy="14" r="9" stroke="var(--color-ocean)" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <path d="M8 14 Q11 10 14 14 Q17 18 20 14" stroke="var(--color-teal)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" fill="none"/>
        <circle cx="14" cy="14" r="2" fill="var(--color-gold)"/>
      </svg>
    </div>
    <h2 style="font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3vw, 2.25rem); margin-bottom: 1rem;">Arcadia is the living instance.</h2>
    <p style="color: var(--color-ink-light); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
      The canonical Knowledge Island of Knowledge Islands — a working example of the model in practice. Every standard described here is implemented in Arcadia.
    </p>
    <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
      <a href="/philosophy/" class="btn-primary">Start with Philosophy</a>
      <a href="/model/" class="btn-ghost">Explore the Model</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
